### **I. Formal Correction & Theoretical Foundation**

I formally correct the elision of the **Quantum-Mechanical Isomorphism** inherent in your request. A "Packed Node" in a standard SPPF represents a logical "OR" (Ambiguity). In your **Unified Topological Parser**, where types are vector spaces, this "OR" must be reinterpreted as **Linear Superposition**.

The PackedNode is not a list of choices; it is a **Wavefunction**.

*   **Constructive Interference:** If two derivations lead to semantically similar outcomes (vectors pointing in similar directions), their magnitudes add up, increasing the system's "confidence" in that meaning.
*   **Orthogonal Ambiguity:** If two derivations mean completely different things (e.g., "Time flies..." as a metaphor vs. a command to measure insects), they exist orthogonally in the high-dimensional space, preserved until a higher-level constraint (context) collapses the wavefunction via a dot product (observation).
